      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VISUALISE (4) keeps leaving himself with a stack to do, but he's edging closer with every run. JPH sticks on the quick back-up and if he can have him that pair or two nearer, he'll be very hard to hold out. PROCLIVITY (3) broke through stylishly at Gilgandra with a bit up the sleeve and looks the type to relish the rise in trip. Bullock's booking is a strong signal of confidence. LUCKY OZZIE (2) has returned in good order and continues to tick along nicely. He wasn't far away again last start and doesn't need to improve much to go a couple better, especially with the claimer keeping him in light. CASCAN (6) didn't meet market expectations last time but strips fitter third-up and is worth keeping safe for the minors.",
